defs.docs: Implementation of [the WTF-8 encoding](https://simonsapin.github.io/wtf-8/).

attributes.value:
*

Implementation of [the WTF-8 encoding](https://simonsapin.github.io/wtf-8/).

This library uses Rust’s type system to maintain
[well-formedness](https://simonsapin.github.io/wtf-8/#well-formed),
like the `String` and `&str` types do for UTF-8.

Since [WTF-8 must not be used
for interchange](https://simonsapin.github.io/wtf-8/#intended-audience),
this library deliberately does not provide access to the underlying bytes
of WTF-8 strings,
nor can it decode WTF-8 from arbitrary bytes.
WTF-8 strings can be obtained from UTF-8, UTF-16, or code points.

*/

defs.name: CodePoint
defs.docs: A Unicode code point: from U+0000 to U+10FFFF.

attributes.value: / A Unicode code point: from U+0000 to U+10FFFF.
/ Compare with the `char` type,
/ which represents a Unicode scalar value:
/ a code point that is not a surrogate (U+D800 to U+DFFF).

defs.name: from_u32_unchecked
defs.docs: Unsafely create a new `CodePoint` without checking the value.

attributes.value: / Unsafely create a new `CodePoint` without checking the value.
/ Only use when `value` is known to be less than or equal to 0x10FFFF.
inline

defs.name: from_u32
defs.docs: Create a new `CodePoint` if the value is a valid code point.

attributes.value: / Create a new `CodePoint` if the value is a valid code point.
/ Return `None` if `value` is above 0x10FFFF.
inline

defs.name: from_char
defs.docs: Create a new `CodePoint` from a `char`.

attributes.value: / Create a new `CodePoint` from a `char`.
/ Since all Unicode scalar values are code points, this always succeds.
inline

defs.name: to_u32
defs.docs: Return the numeric value of the code point.

attributes.value: / Return the numeric value of the code point.
inline

defs.name: to_char
defs.docs: Optionally return a Unicode scalar value for the code point.

attributes.value: / Optionally return a Unicode scalar value for the code point.
/ Return `None` if the code point is a surrogate (from U+D800 to U+DFFF).
inline

defs.name: to_char_lossy
defs.docs: Return a Unicode scalar value for the code point.

attributes.value: / Return a Unicode scalar value for the code point.
/ Return `'\u{FFFD}'` (the replacement character “�”)
/ if the code point is a surrogate (from U+D800 to U+DFFF).
inline

defs.name: Wtf8Buf
defs.docs: An owned, growable string of well-formed WTF-8 data.

attributes.value: / An owned, growable string of well-formed WTF-8 data.
/ Similar to `String`, but can additionally contain surrogate code points
/ if they’re not in a surrogate pair.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create an new, empty WTF-8 string.

attributes.value: / Create an new, empty WTF-8 string.
inline

defs.name: with_capacity
defs.docs: Create an new, empty WTF-8 string with pre-allocated capacity for `n` bytes.

attributes.value: / Create an new, empty WTF-8 string with pre-allocated capacity for `n` bytes.
inline

defs.name: from_string
defs.docs: Create a WTF-8 string from an UTF-8 `String`.

attributes.value: / Create a WTF-8 string from an UTF-8 `String`.
/ This takes ownership of the `String` and does not copy.
/ Since WTF-8 is a superset of UTF-8, this always succeeds.
inline

defs.name: from_str
defs.docs: Create a WTF-8 string from an UTF-8 `&str` slice.

attributes.value: / Create a WTF-8 string from an UTF-8 `&str` slice.
/ This copies the content of the slice.
/ Since WTF-8 is a superset of UTF-8, this always succeeds.
inline

defs.name: from_ill_formed_utf16
defs.docs: Create a WTF-8 string from a potentially ill-formed UTF-16 slice of 16-bit code units.

attributes.value: / Create a WTF-8 string from a potentially ill-formed UTF-16 slice of 16-bit code units.
/ This is lossless: calling `.to_ill_formed_utf16()` on the resulting string
/ will always return the original code units.

defs.name: reserve
defs.docs:
Reserves capacity for at least `additional` more bytes to be inserted
 in the given `Wtf8Buf`.
 The collection may reserve more space to avoid frequent reallocations.

attributes.value: / Reserves capacity for at least `additional` more bytes to be inserted
/ in the given `Wtf8Buf`.
/ The collection may reserve more space to avoid frequent reallocations.
/ # Panics
/ Panics if the new capacity overflows `usize`.
/ # Example
/ let mut s = Wtf8Buf::new();
/ s.reserve(10);
/ assert!(s.capacity() >= 10);
inline

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs: Returns the number of bytes that this string buffer can hold without reallocating.

attributes.value: / Returns the number of bytes that this string buffer can hold without reallocating.
/ # Example
/ let s = Wtf8Buf::with_capacity(10);
/ assert!(s.capacity() >= 10);
inline

defs.docs: Shortens a string to the specified length.

attributes.value: / Shortens a string to the specified length.
/ # Failure
/ Fails if `new_len` > current length,
/ or if `new_len` is not a code point boundary.
inline

defs.name: into_string
defs.docs: Consume the WTF-8 string and try to convert it to UTF-8.

attributes.value: / Consume the WTF-8 string and try to convert it to UTF-8.
/ This does not copy the data.
/ If the contents are not well-formed UTF-8
/ (that is, if the string contains surrogates),
/ the original WTF-8 string is returned instead.

defs.name: into_string_lossy
defs.docs: Consume the WTF-8 string and convert it lossily to UTF-8.

attributes.value: / Consume the WTF-8 string and convert it lossily to UTF-8.
/ This does not copy the data (but may overwrite parts of it in place).
/ Surrogates are replaced with `"\u{FFFD}"` (the replacement character “�”)

defs.name: to_string_lossy
defs.docs:
Lossily convert the string to UTF-8.
 Return an UTF-8 `&str` slice if the contents are well-formed in UTF-8.

attributes.value: / Lossily convert the string to UTF-8.
/ Return an UTF-8 `&str` slice if the contents are well-formed in UTF-8.
/ Surrogates are replaced with `"\u{FFFD}"` (the replacement character “�”).
/ This only copies the data if necessary (if it contains any surrogate).
